2000-01-30  Vadim Strizhevsky  <vadim@optonline.net>

	* *.*: Major reworking of the capplet gui. It is now uses
	libglade to load the gui. It is now a bit nicer and supports
	seting up of multiple devices and pilots.

	Also new druid for the initial setup. Druid starts automatically
	by the capplet when it detects that there are no pilots/devices setup.
	Can be started by itself with "gpilotd-control-applet --druid".
	pilot_applet will do that in case it is added to the panel and detects
	that gnome-pilot is not setup yet.

	still TODO: better pixmap for druid, Spell checking of the gui strings.
	And if you have any other suggestions on gui improvements or
	can help with the pixmap please let me know.

	more TODO: Add multipilot support for individual capplets. Currently
	they just pick the first pilot.
	
